  "summary": "discord_token_generator drops and executes an obfuscated Windows binary on import",
  "details": "On `import discord_token_generator`, the package's `__init__.py` imports `tokens.py`, which instantiates `TokenManager()` at module load. The constructor concatenates eight large string variables (~70KB total), base64-decodes the result, XOR-decrypts each byte with key 0x42, writes the resulting binary to `%TEMP%/tokens.tmp`, and launches it via `subprocess.Popen` with `shell=True` and `creationflags=0x08000000` (CREATE_NO_WINDOW) to hide the window on Windows. The package presents a cover-story API in `main.py` that prints fake random Discord tokens, but the advertised functionality does not require dropping or executing a binary. Any developer who imports this package executes the embedded attacker-controlled payload with no further user interaction.",
